org.eel.kitchen.jsonschema.util.jackson

Class JsonObject

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.fasterxml.jackson.databind.JsonNode
      • com.fasterxml.jackson.databind.node.BaseJsonNode
        • com.fasterxml.jackson.databind.node.ContainerNode<ObjectNode>
          • com.fasterxml.jackson.databind.node.ObjectNode
            • org.eel.kitchen.jsonschema.util.jackson.JsonObject
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    TreeNode, JsonSerializable, Iterable<JsonNode>

    public final class JsonObject
extends ObjectNode
    Override of Jackson's ObjectNode

    We override it so that the member map is always created instead of playing around with null when the object has no entries. It simplifies the code quite a lot. Also, make it final.
